<TITLE> Dhaka backs UN reforms: Iftekhar </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Oct 4 (bdnews24.com) The foreign adviser has given Bangladesh's backing to reform initiatives of the United Nations. Bangladesh will play an active role in supporting reforms in line with aspirations of least developed countries, said Iftekhar Ahmed Chowdhury in a statement from New York. After a meeting with president of the 63rd UN General Assembly Dr Miguel D'Escoto Brockman, on Friday, Iftekhar said the UNGA president had praised Bangladesh for its participation in the United Nations. Brockman also said he looked forward to working more closely with Bangladesh during his tenure. The adviser invited the UNGA president to visit Bangladesh. bdn
